                            Known as the Passport Man of India, Mulay, who opened over 500 passport
                            offices nationwide, guides the foundation's activities daily. The foundation's
                            inception aimed at providing immediate aid to recent flood victims in
                            Kolhapur and Sangli. It has spearheaded several projects including
                            distribution of clothing, educational fee payments for village students, and
                            the adoption and rehabilitation of two villages by Mulay himself.
                            Aligned with Mulay's vision, the foundation focuses on housing provision,
                            livelihood reconstruction, employment creation, and provision of other
                            facilities to villagers, aimed at economic and managerial self-reliance. It
                            also works towards preparing individuals for independent disaster
                            management and equips them financially to enhance their quality of life.
